pes(None)` → `[]`\n2. `parse_scopes(\"\")` → `[]`\n3. `parse_scopes(\"read\")` → `[\"read\"]`\n4. `parse_scopes(\"read write profile\")` → `[\"read\", \"write\", \"profile\"]`\n5. `parse_scopes(\"  read  write  \")` → `[\"read\", \"write\"]` (extra whitespace ignored)\n6. `parse_scopes(\"read read\")` → `[\"read\", \"read\"]` (duplicates preserved)\n7. `validate_scopes([\"read\"], [\"read\", \"write\"])` → `True`\n8. `validate_scopes([\"admin\"], [\"read\", \"write\"])` → `False`\n9. `validate_scopes([], [\"read\"])` → `True`\n10. `validate_scopes([\"read\", \"write\"], [\"write\", \"read\"])` → `True` (order-independent)\n11. `validate_scopes(\"read write\", [\"read\"])` raises `ValueError` (string is not list-like for requested)\n12. `validate_scopes([\"read\"], \"read write\")` raises `ValueError` (string is not list-like for allowed)\n\nNote: strings are *not* considered valid list-like iterables for this function — passing a plain string for either parameter must raise `ValueError`.",
